Hello ,
I hope I could answer all the doubts you had over the call on the same day of this review.
This reply is for others going through your review on our page .
You have visited our facility in March and we have advised you for an RCT..
you have revisited us in July with pain in that tooth which was severely infected as you have delayed treatment for 4 months.
That is the reason we took three appointments for RCT as we cannot fill it until the infection comes down.(3 appointments along with crown fixing in a span of 10 days)
All the appointments were done under anesthesia ,
yes, you might have had pain during the procedure, if infection was very active.
About the price-you said u want to go with the best ..we fabricated the crown with an INTRAORAL SCANNER(very rarely available in any dental facility, for accuracy ,instead of gooey impressions)
-and from DENTCARE-best possible crown you can opt for.
alternatively, we have given price options starting from 2000INR.
And lastly we give enough time for everyone, for shade matching and acceptance of the crown .
yes in a mirror-only possible option without any color hue and saturation differences if seen in cameras and screens,(the small mirror is the mouth mirror used to show back teeth).
..and coming to the size of your crown ,
you had an RCT for a molar and you are comparing your tooth to a premolar which is definitely smaller in size.
And if you are comparing it with the opposite corresponding molar of the same jaw, the amount of structure remaining in your natural tooth after removing the caries, decides the size of final prosthesis to prevent fractures.
please consider the fact that all the teeth do not have the same anatomy.
also scaling visible stains if removable(if not fluorosis or smoking stains)-will be removed completely.
other than those-shade of the teeth wont change with basic scaling.
hope this helps,
thank you!
